cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CC 

The paper deals with capacity approximations for a Gaussian relay network, which involves information theory and communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves network coding and signal processing, which are relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of codebooks, which is relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and the quantization of signals, which is relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
